<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-23T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-23T16:00:00-05:00" n="874" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d874">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.622a/213a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chargé in Great
                                Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LIB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-23T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>For <persName corresp="#p_GHS1">Gibson</persName>.<note n="1" xml:id="d874fn1">Secretary of Embassy.</note> Crewe promised to give
                            me names, ages, status of those taken from <hi rend="italic">China</hi>.
                            Please procure them and send to the Department. The Secretary instructs
                            me again to request immediate release of these men. I asked his consent
                            to my asking you to remind <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Grey</persName>
                            and telegraph as early definite answer as possible instead of sending
                            another formal note and protest against longer detention.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>